    quiz: [{"question": "The D-zone test (disk approximation) detects:", "options": ["ESBL production", "Carbapenemase activity", "Inducible clindamycin resistance mediated by erm genes in staphylococci and streptococci", "Beta-lactamase production"], "correctIndex": 2, "rationale": "D-zone test: erythromycin disk placed 15-20mm from clindamycin disk. Flattened (D-shaped) zone around clindamycin adjacent to erythromycin = inducible erm-mediated resistance. Erythromycin induces methylase production that also confers clindamycin resistance. Report as 'clindamycin resistant (inducible)' per CLSI."}]
