    pearls: ["A Ct value above 35-38 should be interpreted with caution as it may represent contamination or non-specific amplification near the limit of detection", "Internal controls must amplify in every negative specimen to confirm that extraction and amplification were successful and rule out inhibition", "NGS library preparation quality directly impacts sequencing accuracy and depth of coverage"],
    quiz: [{"question": "In real-time PCR, a lower Ct (cycle threshold) value indicates:", "options": ["Lower target concentration", "Higher target concentration in the original sample", "PCR inhibition", "Non-specific amplification"], "correctIndex": 1, "rationale": "Ct value is inversely proportional to the starting amount of target nucleic acid. High initial target = fewer cycles needed to reach fluorescent threshold = lower Ct. Low Ct (e.g., 15-20) = high concentration. High Ct (e.g., 35-40) = low concentration near LOD."}]
