    quiz: [{"question": "A patient has ALP 450 U/L (elevated) and GGT 15 U/L (normal). The most likely source of the elevated ALP is:", "options": ["Liver disease", "Bone disease — normal GGT excludes hepatobiliary source of ALP elevation", "Pancreatic disease", "Renal disease"], "correctIndex": 1, "rationale": "ALP is present in liver, bone, intestine, and placenta. GGT is specific to hepatobiliary system. Elevated ALP with normal GGT = bone source (Paget's disease, osteomalacia, bone metastases, growth in children). Elevated ALP with elevated GGT = hepatobiliary source."}]
